snippet.textDisplay: think about it, this thing had been following Corey and his family for years and years after being brought up by Corey using the original ouija board... it’s had no real way of communicating beside showing itself and messing with the surroundings ever since Corey stopped using the board.  Then, FINALLY, years later, Corey has the courage to fly back to where it all started and to use the original board that summoned this spirit. And FINALLY give the spirit the chance to say what’s been on it’s mind for the past decade.... but you only gave it a few minutes to act. You can’t sum up more than a decade of thoughts and pain in the few short minutes you allowed. It could have been trying to muster up what it wanted to say because it knew that it only had a limited amount of time to speak with you. Because it knew you would get scared and end the session if it spoke without haste... when you closed the board the first time it gave you clear signs it wanted to speak to you, and before it could figure out what to spell or how to get it’s message across, you closed the board the final time. OF COURSE it’s gonna get angry! Of course it’s gonna do everything in its power to show you it was really there, and that it wanted to talk to you. You just didn’t give it enough time.
